    <div class="faq-wrap fu fd1">
      <div class="faq-row">
        <button class="faq-btn" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-a1" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Do you only build AI agents, or do you build full software products too?<span class="faq-ic">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-body" id="faq-a1"><div class="faq-inner">Both. We build autonomous AI agent systems (multi-agent pipelines for sales, ops, and support) and full AI-first software products (SaaS platforms, internal tools, vertical apps). The common thread is that AI is the core architecture in everything we build — not a feature bolted on afterward. If you have a workflow to automate or a product to build, we can help with either.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-row">
        <button class="faq-btn" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-a2" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What's the difference between AI-first software and just adding AI to an app?<span class="faq-ic">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-body" id="faq-a2"><div class="faq-inner">Traditional software is built around manual workflows, then AI is added as a feature — usually a chatbot or a search bar. AI-first means we design the AI layer before anything else: what should the model handle, what data does it need, how does it interact with the rest of the system? The result is software where AI handles the heavy lifting on every core workflow, not just one bolt-on feature. It's a fundamentally different architecture, and it results in software that gets smarter as it's used.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-row">
        <button class="faq-btn" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-a3" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How is this different from Zapier, Make, or a chatbot?<span class="faq-ic">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-body" id="faq-a3"><div class="faq-inner">Automation tools like Zapier move data between apps — they don't reason, adapt, or make decisions. Chatbots respond to questions. Our agent systems research context, evaluate options, write original content, coordinate across multiple tools, and take action autonomously. Think of the difference between an automation rule and an employee who uses judgment.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-row">
        <button class="faq-btn" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-a4" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How long does a typical project take?<span class="faq-ic">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-body" id="faq-a4"><div class="faq-inner">Agent systems: 3–5 weeks in production. Simple single-agent integrations can be live in 2 weeks. AI-first software products: 4–8 weeks for an MVP, depending on scope. We give you a precise timeline in the scoped proposal after the discovery call — we never commit before we understand what we're building.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-row">
        <button class="faq-btn" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-a5" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What does it cost?<span class="faq-ic">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-body" id="faq-a5"><div class="faq-inner">Agent system builds start from $8,000. Most complete agent systems are in the $10,000–$15,000 range. AI-first software MVPs typically start from $12,000 depending on scope and integrations. All engagements are fixed-price — no hourly billing. Monthly retainers for ongoing evolution start at $2,500/month. All pricing is confirmed in the scoped proposal after the discovery call.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-row">
        <button class="faq-btn" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-a6" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Do you work with early-stage startups?<span class="faq-ic">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-body" id="faq-a6"><div class="faq-inner">Yes — some of our best-fit engagements are early-stage products where the founding team wants to build AI-first from the start rather than retrofit later. The earlier you bring AI into the architecture, the better the outcome. That said, we need a clear scope and a realistic budget conversation — we don't do exploratory builds on equity alone.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-row">
        <button class="faq-btn" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-a7" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Do you sign NDAs?<span class="faq-ic">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-body" id="faq-a7"><div class="faq-inner">Yes. We're happy to sign a mutual NDA before the discovery call. Most of our case studies are anonymised for this reason. If you have sensitive processes or data requirements, let us know before we start.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-row">
        <button class="faq-btn" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-a8" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What happens if you're at capacity, or I need support after launch?<span class="faq-ic">+</span></button>
